    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-23T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/8730</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-23T10:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 25, 7.25 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2921. From reliable source it is reported that German Government is furious at
                    Professor <persName corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName> in Vienna, and German
                    Embassy made definite complaint to Austrian Government that <persName
                        corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName> was engaged in pernicious agitation
                    against Germany. It is stated that the representations amounted to a precipitate
                    ultimatum. It was demanded that Emperor <persName>Charles</persName> disapprove
                        <persName corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName> or face prospect of German
                    occupation of Vienna. Austrian Government was obliged to make evasion and
                    tentative disavowal of <persName corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName>’s
                    negotiations in Switzerland. Emperor personally stands by <persName
                        corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName> and latter has announced he will fight
                    to death to complete Austrian federation with autonomous states, complete
                    separation from German policy, and a reorientation in accord with the Western
                    Powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
